d 'CLUSTERDID': module providing power analysis for cluster randomized trials, difference-in-differences sample size, and repeated cross-sections
d
d      clusterdid establishes a generalized, parallel-group
d difference-in-differences (DiD)    cluster randomized trial
d framework observed over a longitudinal panel of T = T0 + T1	
d periods. It integrates the multi-way and nested error component
d models from Baltagi	 (2021) to capture permanent and
d time-varying cluster shocks.	  Unlike legacy power commands
d restricted to single post-treatment snapshots or purely   
d standardized metrics, clusterdid natively accommodates
d multi-period repeated    cross-sections, allowing researchers to
d evaluate how expanding baseline and endline	 tracking horizons
d mathematically reduces the variance multiplier. 
d
d KW: power analysis
d KW: DiD
d KW: randomized trial
d
d Requires: Stata version 
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260524
d
d Author: Wael Moussa,    FHI 360
d Support: email wmoussa@@fhi360.org
d
